ydides uses rigorous principles of selection, suggestive juxtapositions, and artfully opposed speeches to reveal systematic relationships between plans and outcomes, impose meaning on the smallest events, and insist on the constant battle between intellect and chance. Thucydides’ mind found in unity and coherence its ideal of historical truth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAncient History & Classical Studies. 4aHistory. 4aLiterary Studies.  aclassical philosophy, Thucydides, Peloponnesian War, Thucydidean scholarship, classical literacy.1 aRawlings, Elizabeth Trapnell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRawlings, Hunter R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRusten, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171974540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501719745423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501719745/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles